	url = {http://scientiamarina.revistas.csic.es/index.php/scientiamarina/article/view/744/761},
	doi = {10.3989/scimar.2000.64n197},
	abstract = {SUMMARY: The reproduction of the cutlassfish Trichiurus lepturus was studied from samples collected in bottom trawl surveys 63.9 cm on the continental shelf for males and 69.3 cm and shelf break off for females. Batch southern Brazil. The mean total fecundity ranged from 3,917 in alesnpgethci(mLeT)n at first gonadal of 70 cm LT to maturity 154,216 was in a specimen of 141 cm but the number of spawning batches in each season was not established. Spawning occurs in late spring and summer in the continental shelf and probably year round over the shelf break. High surface temperatures and moderate stratification of the water column were associated with the final stages of gonadal maturation. Seasonal and spatial differences in sex ratios, sizes, maturity stages and feeding intensities suggest that adult female T. lepturus remain during the cold season in the continental shelf of southern Brazil to feed, while adult males move to warmer waters northward or offshore.},
